<!-- FAQ -->
<section class="content-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-header">
      <span class="section-label">FAQ</span>
      <h2>AC Installation Questions</h2>
      <p>Common questions about air conditioning installation in Hawaii.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <details class="faq-details">
        <summary>How long does AC installation take?</summary>
        <div class="faq-details-body">
          <p>Most residential AC installations take 1-2 days depending on the system type. Mini-split installations are typically faster (4-8 hours), while central air systems may take 1-2 days. We'll provide an accurate timeline during your free estimate.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-details">
        <summary>What AC brands do you install?</summary>
        <div class="faq-details-body">
          <p>We install all major AC brands including Daikin, Mitsubishi, Carrier, Trane, Lennox, and more. We'll recommend the best system for your Hawaii home based on your needs, budget, and home specifications.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-details">
        <summary>Do you offer financing for AC installation?</summary>
        <div class="faq-details-body">
          <p>Yes, we offer financing options to make your AC installation more affordable. Contact us at (808) 664-5751 to learn about current financing programs.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-details">
        <summary>How do I choose between mini-split and central air?</summary>
        <div class="faq-details-body">
          <p>Mini-splits are great for homes without existing ductwork, room additions, and when you want zone control. Central air works well if you have ductwork and want whole-home cooling from a single outdoor unit. We'll help you decide based on your home and budget during the free assessment.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-details">
        <summary>What size AC do I need?</summary>
        <div class="faq-details-body">
          <p>The right size depends on your home's square footage, insulation, ceiling height, windows, and sun exposure. Oversized systems waste energy and don't dehumidify properly. Undersized systems run constantly. We perform proper load calculations to size your system correctly.</p>
        </div>
      </details>

      <details class="faq-details">
        <summary>Is there a warranty on the installation?</summary>
        <div class="faq-details-body">
          <p>Yes! Equipment comes with manufacturer warranties (typically 5-10 years on parts, 1 year on labor). We also stand behind our installation workmanship. We'll register your warranty and provide all documentation.</p>
        </div>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

